Author::::misterbaxter
DateTime::::2016-03-01T22:54:41Z
I don't think you've understood the story. The UK is legally bound to meet certain targets on air pollution. Client Earth are merely moving the issue through the courts so that the courts can consider whether the government is in breach of this legal duty. Client Earth didn't make the laws; we signed up to them via the EU. if we leave the EU we can opt out and stick with our primitive and polluting transport system, if that's what the people want, but as things stand, the government does not appear to be acting legally.



